I don't think anything. Why?

748
01:16:28,061 --> 01:16:29,639
Nothing.

749
01:16:29,729 --> 01:16:31,473
I was just wondering, that's all.

750
01:16:32,565 --> 01:16:36,433
There's nothing to wonder.
It's a business arrangement, that's all.

751
01:16:40,407 --> 01:16:42,779
And his ship sails tomorrow, like he said.

752
01:16:45,036 --> 01:16:46,447
Like he said.

753
01:16:58,925 --> 01:17:00,882
Good God.

754
01:17:00,969 --> 01:17:02,214
I can't drink all that.

755
01:17:02,304 --> 01:17:05,340
No, but I know a man who can.

756
01:17:12,731 --> 01:17:14,225
Cheers.

757
01:17:16,985 --> 01:17:19,476
Since when did you start smoking those?

758
01:17:19,571 --> 01:17:21,148
What happened to your roll-ups?

759
01:17:29,080 --> 01:17:31,452
Oh, Jesus. Make my next one a double.

760
01:17:34,002 --> 01:17:36,707
# When I was a young man

761
01:17:36,796 --> 01:17:39,122
# I used to dream of a maiden...

762
01:17:40,925 --> 01:17:42,170
That's my song.

763
01:17:42,302 --> 01:17:44,674
# With long soft hair

764
01:17:45,805 --> 01:17:48,427
# Blowing in the wind

765
01:17:51,478 --> 01:17:56,768
# Her laughing eyes
and loving arms would follow

766
01:17:59,444 --> 01:18:01,437
# When I'd sail around the world...

767
01:18:01,529 --> 01:18:03,902
Hey, Frankie. Hey, Frankie.

768
01:18:03,990 --> 01:18:09,329
I bet you all your trump cards
that you don't ask Catriona Murray to dance.

769
01:18:10,830 --> 01:18:14,496
# I'd ride down on a great white horse...

770
01:18:15,669 --> 01:18:18,919
If you do that, I'll get your mum up to dance.

771
01:18:20,256 --> 01:18:21,799
Deal?

772
01:18:23,551 --> 01:18:26,303
# I'd bring her laughter...

773
01:18:26,388 --> 01:18:27,633
Dance?

774
01:18:27,722 --> 01:18:30,178
# On a rainy day...

775
01:18:30,266 --> 01:18:32,224
I never dance.

776
01:18:33,353 --> 01:18:36,804
You'll have to this once.
Frankie's made another bet.

777
01:18:38,483 --> 01:18:41,769
You'd better watch him.
It's becoming a bit of a habit.

778
01:18:50,203 --> 01:18:55,494
# When I was a young girl,
I used to dream of a lover

779
01:18:58,878 --> 01:19:05,332
# Who'd be my shining knight
of strength one day

780
01:19:06,886 --> 01:19:12,129
# He'd take me to a castle in the heavens

781
01:19:15,437 --> 01:19:21,807
# And battle all my dragons on the way

782
01:19:22,736 --> 01:19:29,866
# And he'd ride down on a great white horse

783
01:19:31,244 --> 01:19:34,743
# He'd give me love

784
01:19:34,831 --> 01:19:38,282
# I'd been longing for

785
01:19:39,294 --> 01:19:43,244
# He'd bring me joy

786
01:19:43,340 --> 01:19:47,551
# And lasting peace

787
01:19:47,636 --> 01:19:51,680
# And on a great white horse

788
01:19:51,765 --> 01:19:54,635
# He'd ride away with me...

789
01:20:15,538 --> 01:20:19,073
Uno, dos, tres, cuatro.

790
01:20:19,376 --> 01:20:23,041
Uno, dos, tres, cuatro!

791
01:20:24,547 --> 01:20:26,505
I had a good time tonight.

792
01:20:29,719 --> 01:20:31,676
Don't sound so surprised.

793
01:20:34,224 --> 01:20:37,011
You are the best!

794
01:20:37,102 --> 01:20:39,059
He's got your eyes.

795
01:20:42,357 --> 01:20:43,935
They pull you.

796
01:20:44,985 --> 01:20:46,230
Right in.

797
01:20:46,319 --> 01:20:49,273
Uno, dos, tres, cuatro.

798
01:20:49,364 --> 01:20:51,321
I don't know what to say to that.

799
01:20:52,575 --> 01:20:54,615
Well, you don't have to say anything.

800
01:20:59,124 --> 01:21:00,867
You don't have to say nice things to me.

801
01:21:00,959 --> 01:21:02,916
I'm not paying you for that.

802
01:21:05,380 --> 01:21:07,337
So, why don't you want to hear them?

803
01:21:10,385 --> 01:21:12,342
What are you afraid of?

804
01:21:15,765 --> 01:21:17,722
Where did Marie find you?

805
01:21:19,769 --> 01:21:21,477
No.

806
01:21:22,522 --> 01:21:24,479
I thought we agreed: No history.

807
01:21:31,948 --> 01:21:33,905
Things have changed.

808
01:21:37,787 --> 01:21:39,330
Have they?

809
01:21:43,960 --> 01:21:48,337
What I find really difficult...

810
01:21:49,841 --> 01:21:51,798
to understand...

811
01:21:53,011 --> 01:21:54,553
is why?

812
01:21:56,890 --> 01:21:58,966
I told you why. Frankie made a bet.

813
01:21:59,059 --> 01:22:01,597
No, no, no, no, no.

814
01:22:01,686 --> 01:22:06,147
Why did he ever leave the two of you?

815
01:22:12,405 --> 01:22:14,731
He didn't leave us. I left him.

816
01:22:17,869 --> 01:22:21,487
One night I just picked Frankie up, and I left.

817
01:22:21,581 --> 01:22:24,748
And my mother came with me,
to make sure I never went back.

818
01:22:28,463 --> 01:22:30,337
And we've been leaving ever since.

819
01:22:30,423 --> 01:22:33,460
<i>Always ready in case he shows up.</i>

820
01:22:40,600 --> 01:22:44,384
Frankie wasn't born deaf.
It was a present from his daddy.

821
01:23:12,507 --> 01:23:16,125
Frankie's a very... very lucky boy.

822
01:23:19,472 --> 01:23:22,046
How do you figure that one out?

823
01:23:22,142 --> 01:23:24,929
I'm his mother, and I lie to him every single day.

824
01:23:25,020 --> 01:23:26,597
No.

825
01:23:28,315 --> 01:23:30,307
No, you protect him every single day.

826
01:23:35,822 --> 01:23:36,901
Do I?

827
01:23:44,539 --> 01:23:50,044
Every time I write one of those letters
I promise myself it'll be the last one.

828
01:23:51,880 --> 01:23:54,453
<i>I thought he'd lose interest, in time.</i>

829
01:23:55,592 --> 01:23:57,134
<i>Just stop</i>

830
01:24:00,096 --> 01:24:02,422
But see, if he hasn't written
for a couple of weeks,

831
01:24:02,515 --> 01:24:05,801
I'm the one egging him on,
telling him to hurry up and write.

832
01:24:08,730 --> 01:24:10,770
<i>It's the only way I can hear his voice.</i>

833
01:24:58,280 --> 01:24:59,690
<i>I'd better go.</i>

834
01:25:01,408 --> 01:25:02,902
I'm away first thing.

835
01:25:07,205 --> 01:25:08,865
Can I say goodbye?

836
01:25:08,957 --> 01:25:10,617
If you can wake him.

837
01:25:52,000 --> 01:25:53,459
Hey.

838
01:25:56,379 --> 01:25:58,953
You're coming back?

839
01:26:04,429 --> 01:26:06,552
I don't know, Frankie.

840
01:26:35,126 --> 01:26:36,241
Did you do this?

841
01:26:41,466 --> 01:26:44,004
Frankie, I can't take this. This... This is yours.

842
01:26:52,811 --> 01:26:54,768
I'd be honoured to take it.

843
01:26:57,315 --> 01:26:59,107
It's beautiful.

844
01:27:10,120 --> 01:27:12,077
Remember, Frankie.

845
01:27:13,456 --> 01:27:15,414
We're all connected.

846
01:30:35,742 --> 01:30:37,699
Lizzie, Lizzie.

847
01:30:47,128 --> 01:30:48,836
I've let myself go a wee bit. Sorry.

848
01:30:54,094 --> 01:30:56,003
It's been a long time.

849
01:31:01,184 --> 01:31:02,844
You're still beautiful.

850
01:31:04,062 --> 01:31:06,553
No, I'm not. I'm not beautiful.

851
01:31:07,649 --> 01:31:09,440
I'm sorry.

852
01:31:12,779 --> 01:31:14,688
I'm sorry, Lizzie.

853
01:31:15,782 --> 01:31:17,490
I'm sorry, Lizzie.

854
01:31:17,575 --> 01:31:19,734
Shush, Davey. Shush.

855
01:31:21,746 --> 01:31:24,581
It's all right. It's all right now.

856
01:31:26,293 --> 01:31:27,751
Don't cry.

857
01:31:33,758 --> 01:31:35,253
Where's Frankie?

858
01:31:35,343 --> 01:31:37,419
<i>He's at school.</i>

859
01:31:37,512 --> 01:31:40,383
He's nine now, nearly ten.

860
01:31:40,473 --> 01:31:42,051
Aye, I know.

861
01:31:44,853 --> 01:31:46,976
He's top at geography.

862
01:31:48,440 --> 01:31:50,397
I always knew he was clever.

863
01:31:53,194 --> 01:31:54,902
Must take that off you.

864
01:31:54,988 --> 01:31:58,855
I don't think so. You were the one
that could have gone to college.

865
01:32:32,901 --> 01:32:35,226
I want to see him, Lizzie.

866
01:32:35,320 --> 01:32:37,562
I've got a right to see him.

867
01:32:37,656 --> 01:32:39,862
<i>- Don't give me that.</i>
<i>- It's too late for fighting.</i>

868
01:32:39,950 --> 01:32:41,741
<i>Just let me see him.</i>

869
01:32:43,787 --> 01:32:45,744
I want him to know how sorry I am.

870
01:32:48,124 --> 01:32:49,583
He's my son.

871
01:32:49,668 --> 01:32:51,625
He's not your son. He's mine.

872
01:32:53,880 --> 01:32:56,205
You don't deserve him.

873
01:32:56,299 --> 01:32:59,134
You don't deserve his forgiveness.

874
01:33:01,721 --> 01:33:03,299
Christ.

875
01:33:05,809 --> 01:33:07,766
I made one mistake.

876
01:33:09,521 --> 01:33:12,771
One stupid fucking mistake,
and you made me pay.

877
01:33:12,857 --> 01:33:15,230
<i>You've made me pay, all right.</i>

878
01:33:16,403 --> 01:33:18,395
You're a bitch.

879
01:33:19,489 --> 01:33:22,573
<i>You're nothing but a bitch!</i>

880
01:33:24,077 --> 01:33:25,357
I want to see my son!

881
01:33:28,039 --> 01:33:29,415
<i>I've got a right!</i>

882
01:33:29,499 --> 01:33:31,077
I'm his father!

883
01:33:31,167 --> 01:33:32,827
<i>I've got rights!</i>

884
01:33:32,919 --> 01:33:35,873
I've got my rights! I'm his father!

885
01:33:35,964 --> 01:33:37,541
You're not his father!

886
01:33:37,632 --> 01:33:40,882
He's got a different father now, a real father.

887
01:33:40,969 --> 01:33:45,880
A kind, gentle man, who teaches him
to throw stones across the water.

888
01:33:45,974 --> 01:33:47,801
You could never be his father.

889
01:33:47,892 --> 01:33:49,850
I want to see my son!

890
01:33:49,936 --> 01:33:52,261
<i>- Davey, please, no, come on.</i>
<i>- I'm his father!</i>

891
01:33:52,355 --> 01:33:53,470
Davey, no, stop it.

892
01:33:53,565 --> 01:33:54,845
Nurse!

893
01:33:54,941 --> 01:33:56,934
<i>Nurse!</i>

894
01:33:57,068 --> 01:33:58,942
I want to see my son!

895
01:34:12,500 --> 01:34:14,458
Lizzie, wait a minute.

896
01:34:16,379 --> 01:34:19,380
Lizzie, Lizzie, please.

897
01:34:19,466 --> 01:34:21,873
He nearly killed us, Janet!

898
01:34:21,968 --> 01:34:24,044
I know. I know.

899
01:34:25,055 --> 01:34:27,094
He's only got a few days left.

900
01:34:27,182 --> 01:34:29,091
He can't touch you now.

901
01:34:29,976 --> 01:34:31,885
Let him die in peace.

902
01:34:32,687 --> 01:34:34,644
For your own sake.

903
01:35:09,391 --> 01:35:11,763
I want to talk to you. It's very important.

904
01:35:13,937 --> 01:35:15,894
I got a message today from your dad.

905
01:35:19,192 --> 01:35:21,564
He's not very well, Frankie.

906
01:35:21,653 --> 01:35:23,195
He's very, very sick.

907
01:35:25,949 --> 01:35:28,404
But he says he wants you to know he loves you.

908
01:35:30,495 --> 01:35:31,658
Very much.

909
01:36:04,529 --> 01:36:07,863
<i>Dear Da, I thought you'd like this drawing.</i>

910
01:36:07,949 --> 01:36:10,274
<i>I copied it from my book.</i>

911
01:36:10,368 --> 01:36:12,776
<i>Ma says you're not very well.</i>

912
01:36:12,871 --> 01:36:15,160
<i>I hope you feel better soon.</i>

913
01:36:15,248 --> 01:36:17,205
<i>Love from your son, Frankie.</i>

914
01:36:49,407 --> 01:36:51,364
<i>OK, call the crash team.</i>

915
01:36:54,287 --> 01:36:56,778
Please! What is wrong with him?

916
01:36:56,873 --> 01:36:58,996
Let's get the bed down. Come on.

917
01:37:00,085 --> 01:37:02,042
Mrs Morrison?

918
01:37:02,128 --> 01:37:05,711
It might be best if you went
and had a cup of tea just now.

919
01:37:05,799 --> 01:37:09,250
I'll send someone along to find you
as soon as we have any news.

920
01:37:10,345 --> 01:37:12,302
This is for my husband.

921
01:37:13,556 --> 01:37:14,932
It's from our son.

922
01:37:15,016 --> 01:37:16,594
Right.

923
01:37:21,314 --> 01:37:23,106
- Oh, Nurse, erm...
- Yes?

924
01:37:27,612 --> 01:37:29,106
Could you make sure he sees it?

925
01:37:29,197 --> 01:37:30,857
I'll make sure.

926
01:37:40,959 --> 01:37:44,624
<i>Davey Morrison</i>
<i>died peacefully after a long illness.</i>

927
01:37:44,713 --> 01:37:46,705
<i>Father to Frankie.</i>

928
01:38:19,331 --> 01:38:23,494
I know it's a terrible thing to say,
but Davey's finally done you a favour.

929
01:38:23,585 --> 01:38:25,328
It's over now.

930
01:38:29,174 --> 01:38:30,419
Marie?

931
01:38:30,508 --> 01:38:31,789
What?

932
01:38:32,844 --> 01:38:34,635
Who was he?

933
01:38:36,014 --> 01:38:37,757
My brother.

934
01:38:40,727 --> 01:38:42,470
Oh, right.

935
01:38:45,607 --> 01:38:47,564
I've got to go.

936
01:38:50,195 --> 01:38:52,520
- Where are you going?
- I'll see you after.

937
01:38:56,952 --> 01:38:58,612
<i>Do you want me to check the box?</i>

938
01:38:58,703 --> 01:39:00,660
<i>There won't be anything in it.</i>

939
01:39:00,747 --> 01:39:03,320
<i>It'll cost you to have your mail forwarded.</i>

940
01:39:03,416 --> 01:39:06,121
I'll check it for you, hen,
just to be on the safe side.

941
01:39:54,426 --> 01:39:56,881
<i>Thanks for the book.</i>

942
01:39:56,970 --> 01:39:59,924
<i>I've read it all the way through now twice.</i>

943
01:40:01,933 --> 01:40:03,677
<i>I took it into school.</i>

944
01:40:03,768 --> 01:40:05,346
<i>I know you won't mind.</i>

945
01:40:05,437 --> 01:40:07,476
<i>My teacher put it on the nature table.</i>

946
01:40:22,037 --> 01:40:24,610
<i>Miss Mackenzie gave me a gold star.</i>

947
01:40:24,706 --> 01:40:27,873
<i>I've got eight now. Catriona's got 20.</i>

948
01:40:27,959 --> 01:40:31,293
<i>Ricky's only got one, and it's not even gold.</i>

949
01:40:38,678 --> 01:40:39,841
<i>Guess what.</i>

950
01:40:39,929 --> 01:40:41,803
<i>I got into the football team.</i>

951
01:40:41,890 --> 01:40:44,974
<i>Well, the reserves. I'm playing on Saturday.</i>

952
01:40:45,060 --> 01:40:47,551
<i>And guess what else.</i>

953
01:40:47,646 --> 01:40:49,804
<i>I got one wrong in geography this week.</i>

954
01:40:53,944 --> 01:40:55,936
<i>Ma and I had a bit of a shock last week.</i>

955
01:40:57,113 --> 01:41:00,945
<i>My da - my real da - he's been sick.</i>

956
01:41:02,118 --> 01:41:04,574
<i>I think he's been sick for a long time.</i>

957
01:41:04,663 --> 01:41:06,323
<i>Ma never said anything.</i>

958
01:41:06,414 --> 01:41:07,992
<i>But I just knew.</i>

959
01:41:08,083 --> 01:41:11,452
<i>And last week, he died.</i>

960
01:41:11,544 --> 01:41:13,786
<i>I think ma's very sad, inside.</i>

961
01:41:13,880 --> 01:41:15,789
<i>But Marie says time's a great healer,</i>

962
01:41:15,882 --> 01:41:19,796
<i>and Ma's not to worry any more,</i>
<i>cos she's still got me.</i>

963
01:41:20,804 --> 01:41:23,425
<i>Anyway, I've got to go now. My tea's ready.</i>

964
01:41:23,515 --> 01:41:25,803
<i>I hope it's not chips.</i>

965
01:41:25,892 --> 01:41:27,849
<i>I've had them three times this week.</i>

966
01:41:29,312 --> 01:41:32,681
<i>Maybe you'll come and see us one more time.</i>

967
01:41:32,774 --> 01:41:34,932
<i>Maybe next time your ship docks.</i>

968
01:41:35,026 --> 01:41:36,983
<i>Your friend, Frankie.</i>

969
01:41:37,000 --> 01:41:40,057

